result.execSummary:
The defendant Deminica A. Conklin was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: In the event probation is revoked, Defendant would be entitled to Good Time Credit and Huber Privileges.

miscConds.notes: Court orders th defendant to make payments of no less than $75.00 per month commencing March 1, 2016 towards Restitution. In the event that the Defendant is revoked or discharged from probation with outstanding financial obligations, the supervising agent shall notify the Court 10 days prior to the revocation or discharge.  A civil judgment shall be entered against the Defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement action will be used to collect the debt.

Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.

The defendant is to have NO CONTACT with the Wautoma Dollar General. Forms of no contact include but are not limited to: in person, in writing, by phone, through text message, or through a third party intending to circumvent the no contact provision.
Defendant is to comply with any rules/recommendations as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.   DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.

records.addlTxt: 10:09 am case called.  Defendant Deminica A. Conklin in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Resolution reached and stated on record by ADA Anderson. Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Plea: No Contest to Count 1.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC.  Court dismisses and reads-in Counts 2 & 3. Court sentences the defendant to: Impose 75 days WCJ, STAYED and places the defendant on probation for a period of 1 year. If revoked, with Huber and Good Time Credit. No credit for time served. CONDTIONS: Restitution of $741.68, to be paid in increments of no less than $75.00 per month commencing March 1, 2016, No Contact with Wautoma Dollar General.
